<% content_for :title, "Setup" %>

<h1 class="text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-stone-900 mb-2">Setup</h1>
<p class="text-sm text-stone-500 mb-8 max-w-2xl">
  One-time and rare actions for getting Tsundoku going. Once your
  library's in and your Kobo is connected, you won't need to come back
  here often — try <%= link_to "Tools", tools_path, class: "underline hover:text-stone-700" %> for ongoing maintenance.
</p>

<div class="space-y-8 max-w-2xl">
  <%# Calibre import — prominent when the library is empty. %>
  <% if @library_empty %>
    <section class="border border-stone-200 rounded-lg p-6 bg-white">
      <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-stone-900 mb-2">Import your library from Calibre</h2>
      <% if @calibre_db_available %>
        <p class="text-sm text-stone-600 mb-4">
          A Calibre <code class="font-mono text-xs bg-stone-100 px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded">metadata.db</code>
          was detected in your library directory. Click below to import every book it knows
          about — authors, series, tags, identifiers, covers, the whole thing. The import runs
          in the background; progress shows in the banner above.
        </p>
        <% if @calibre_import_in_progress %>
          <p class="text-sm text-amber-700">An import is already running.</p>
        <% else %>
          <%= button_to "Import from Calibre",
                library_import_path,
                method: :post,
                form: { data: { turbo_confirm: "Import the Calibre library now?" } },
                class: "inline-flex items-center px-4 py-2 bg-stone-900 text-white text-sm font-medium rounded-md hover:bg-stone-700 transition cursor-pointer" %>
        <% end %>
      <% else %>
        <p class="text-sm text-stone-600">
          Drop a Calibre library (including its <code class="font-mono text-xs bg-stone-100 px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded">metadata.db</code>)
          into the configured library directory. Once it's there, this section will show an
          import button.
        </p>
      <% end %>
    </section>
  <% end %>

  <%# CWA migration — shown when the bind mount is present. %>
  <% if @cwa_db_available %>
    <section class="border border-stone-200 rounded-lg p-6 bg-white">
      <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-stone-900 mb-2">Migrating from Calibre-Web-Automated?</h2>
      <p class="text-sm text-stone-600 mb-4">
        CWA's <code class="font-mono text-xs bg-stone-100 px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded">app.db</code>
        is mounted. Two rake commands handle the handoff:
      </p>
      <ol class="space-y-4 text-sm text-stone-700">
        <li>
          <p class="mb-1">
            <span class="font-medium">1.</span> Adopt Calibre's
            <code class="font-mono text-xs bg-stone-100 px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded">books.uuid</code>
            as <code class="font-mono text-xs bg-stone-100 px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded">kobo_uuid</code>
            so the Kobo de-dupes against entitlements CWA already pushed:
          </p>
          <pre class="bg-stone-900 text-stone-100 text-xs p-3 rounded-md overflow-x-auto"><code>docker exec -it &lt;container&gt; bin/rails kobo:migrate_from_cwa</code></pre>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p class="mb-1">
            <span class="font-medium">2.</span> Import CWA's per-user sync state and reading
            progress (replace <code>alex</code> / <code>smoketest</code> with the actual
            usernames):
          </p>
          <pre class="bg-stone-900 text-stone-100 text-xs p-3 rounded-md overflow-x-auto"><code>docker exec -it &lt;container&gt; bin/rails 'kobo:import_sync_state_from_cwa[alex,smoketest]'</code></pre>
        </li>
      </ol>
      <p class="text-xs text-stone-500 mt-4">
        After both, trigger a sync from each Kobo. See the
        <%= link_to "README", "https://github.com/mm53bar/tsundoku#migrating-from-calibre-web-automated", target: "_blank", rel: "noopener", class: "underline hover:text-stone-700" %>
        for the full migration story.
      </p>
    </section>
  <% end %>

  <%# All-set state when nothing on the page is actionable. %>
  <% unless @library_empty || @cwa_db_available %>
    <section class="border border-stone-200 rounded-lg p-6 bg-white">
      <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-stone-900 mb-1">You're all set</h2>
      <p class="text-sm text-stone-600">
        Library's populated and there's no CWA data to migrate. For ongoing maintenance like
        re-syncing Calibre or scanning new EPUBs, see
        <%= link_to "Tools", tools_path, class: "underline hover:text-stone-700" %>.
      </p>
    </section>
  <% end %>
</div>
